      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Application\nSoftware",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "center",
      "verticalAlign": "middle",
      "containerId": "nC4mCZK0BbNKDAM15gU67",
      "originalText": "Application\nSoftware",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "xXPPvRIFMtBMF3Gy3TEgW",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 975.22523654425,
      "y": 10721.639414130303,
      "width": 1386,
      "height": 750,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bKQ",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 224844335,
      "version": 2276,
      "versionNonce": 1533694953,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1771347138214,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Utility Software -> those software that help us to run and manage our Operating system smoothly. We dont buy\na system for using utility software, I won't buy a laptop so that I can run task manager or I dont buy \nlaptop so that we can partition or de-fragment our disk. But we might buy a laptop for browsing, to watch\nmovies or play game or for coding, which are diff kind of software called as Application software.\n\n\nWhy MAC looks different from LINUX, why ubuntu looks different than redhat -> due to binaries-> binaries are \nlittle software that gives look and feel to a particular Operating system. these tiny software that may produce\nresults in a little different way and because of that little different, all different being combined together\nwe get a whole new different environment of a Operating System. different OS will have different Binaries.\n\n\nSoftware can't do anything until and unless they communicate with Hardware (RAM, Hardisk, system bus) to make them communicate\nproperly there is a piece of code called Kernel.\n\n\nWhen we run a software it becomes Process, running software is called as Process, Every process will go to kernel\nand kernel will line by line schedule them on processor or make them interact with RAM or system bus or data from \nhardisk to processor , the code to manage all these things is written in kernel.\n\nKernel is software written to make interaction other sofware with hardware.\nKernel balances everything whether it is Utility S/w or Application S/w or Binaries and make communication with\nHardware.\n\nHow kernel handles mutiple request using multithreading using fork like parent process then child process and so on.\ninside one process multiple threads are runnning.\nWhen multiple requests hit a server, the OS kernel can handle them using:\n1️⃣ New process per request (fork model)\n2️⃣ Multiple threads inside one process\n3️⃣ Event-driven async model",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Utility Software -> those software that help us to run and manage our Operating system smoothly. We dont buy\na system for using utility software, I won't buy a laptop so that I can run task manager or I dont buy \nlaptop so that we can partition or de-fragment our disk. But we might buy a laptop for browsing, to watch\nmovies or play game or for coding, which are diff kind of software called as Application software.\n\n\nWhy MAC looks different from LINUX, why ubuntu looks different than redhat -> due to binaries-> binaries are \nlittle software that gives look and feel to a particular Operating system. these tiny software that may produce\nresults in a little different way and because of that little different, all different being combined together\nwe get a whole new different environment of a Operating System. different OS will have different Binaries.\n\n\nSoftware can't do anything until and unless they communicate with Hardware (RAM, Hardisk, system bus) to make them communicate\nproperly there is a piece of code called Kernel.\n\n\nWhen we run a software it becomes Process, running software is called as Process, Every process will go to kernel\nand kernel will line by line schedule them on processor or make them interact with RAM or system bus or data from \nhardisk to processor , the code to manage all these things is written in kernel.\n\nKernel is software written to make interaction other sofware with hardware.\nKernel balances everything whether it is Utility S/w or Application S/w or Binaries and make communication with\nHardware.\n\nHow kernel handles mutiple request using multithreading using fork like parent process then child process and so on.\ninside one process multiple threads are runnning.\nWhen multiple requests hit a server, the OS kernel can handle them using:\n1️⃣ New process per request (fork model)\n2️⃣ Multiple threads inside one process\n3️⃣ Event-driven async model",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "RQPYSjDWm-BsaJxNiYjb9",
