      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1770833002624,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Q -> What happens when we turn(Power) on our system in interview? in Google\nthe thing about interview is every question has some followup question\n\neverything about engineering is so fantastic and so easy because it is made up of 0s and 1s which basically means\neither our electric signal is there or it is not there or off or ON.\n\nwhen we press power on button-> as soon as we do the power on pressing thing, the current flows, electricity flows.\nwhen the electricity flows basically the signal which was earlier 0, now the signal is completed which means there\nis input 1 going on",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Q -> What happens when we turn(Power) on our system in interview? in Google\nthe thing about interview is every question has some followup question\n\neverything about engineering is so fantastic and so easy because it is made up of 0s and 1s which basically means\neither our electric signal is there or it is not there or off or ON.\n\nwhen we press power on button-> as soon as we do the power on pressing thing, the current flows, electricity flows.\nwhen the electricity flows basically the signal which was earlier 0, now the signal is completed which means there\nis input 1 going on",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "Hy16ikHMF6kEIMui5n8la",
