      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "we forget about ROM we usually see, RAM size in our Laptop or system why?\nthere are things in ROM, but these things are not written by us, there is a software that comes pre-installed in \nROM, and that pre-installed software is called as BIOS, this BIOS software wait for this 1 input and as soon as\nwe hit this 1, the BIOS starts executing(running).\n\nWhen we press Power on button, Apple sign or Dell sign comes into screen, a software is running in background that\nis call BIOS.\n\nWhat BIOS software is doing in backend -> \n1. It is checking all our hardware parts are connected properly or not like is our HDD existing, Do we have a proper\ncos cell that continues or runs the date and time? Is our system Fan connected properly? Are our system bus working\nproperly all of things are working properly or not the checking of this functionality is the part of BIOS. IT basically\nchecks necessary Hardware which are used to run our system, nothing apart from that.\n\n\nSO our first part as soon as we turn on our system, our first step is BIOS being executed again this has a code\nwhich has certain parameter what to execute first and what next and if we want to skip some part or continue some\npart for a longer period of time we can go to bios screen and try to modify them.\nBIOS part is written in ROM, We have not yet communicated with our HDD or RAM or anything else, it is just ROM\ngiving the data to processor so that it can process and start our system, Now to start our system, the first thing that\nwe need is a Operating System. We need some software that can understand or work on that hardware. that software is our\nOperating system. To load that OS ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "we forget about ROM we usually see, RAM size in our Laptop or system why?\nthere are things in ROM, but these things are not written by us, there is a software that comes pre-installed in \nROM, and that pre-installed software is called as BIOS, this BIOS software wait for this 1 input and as soon as\nwe hit this 1, the BIOS starts executing(running).\n\nWhen we press Power on button, Apple sign or Dell sign comes into screen, a software is running in background that\nis call BIOS.\n\nWhat BIOS software is doing in backend -> \n1. It is checking all our hardware parts are connected properly or not like is our HDD existing, Do we have a proper\ncos cell that continues or runs the date and time? Is our system Fan connected properly? Are our system bus working\nproperly all of things are working properly or not the checking of this functionality is the part of BIOS. IT basically\nchecks necessary Hardware which are used to run our system, nothing apart from that.\n\n\nSO our first part as soon as we turn on our system, our first step is BIOS being executed again this has a code\nwhich has certain parameter what to execute first and what next and if we want to skip some part or continue some\npart for a longer period of time we can go to bios screen and try to modify them.\nBIOS part is written in ROM, We have not yet communicated with our HDD or RAM or anything else, it is just ROM\ngiving the data to processor so that it can process and start our system, Now to start our system, the first thing that\nwe need is a Operating System. We need some software that can understand or work on that hardware. that software is our\nOperating system. To load that OS ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
