      "seed": 1887682092,
      "version": 233,
      "versionNonce": 1321248532,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1770834422502,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1 BIOS getting executed, my hardware will be checked those are properly\nconnected or not. if hardware are connected properly, BIOS redirect us to the\nlocation known as MVR\n2 MBR(Master Boot Record) -> ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1 BIOS getting executed, my hardware will be checked those are properly\nconnected or not. if hardware are connected properly, BIOS redirect us to the\nlocation known as MVR\n2 MBR(Master Boot Record) -> ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "6ohrVAhJr3B5zvJj28YjK",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1009.5465931223429,
      "y": 15166.611795156918,
      "width": 1331,
      "height": 250,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bLT",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1785193388,
      "version": 740,
      "versionNonce": 2089798343,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1771354000887,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Q Why system has lot of memory like HDD, RAM \nHDD has mechanical movement inside it, means it has reading writing head, that head actually mechanically moves up, down\nleft,right, forward,backwards, no matter how fast we are doing mechanical movement it will always be slower as compared \nto a electrical movement or movement of electricity. thats why we say our RAM is a primary memory because it is running \non electricity, As soon as power supply is gone the data in RAM is also gone. because it is all current, it is working on\nelectric current. whereas in harddisk whatever we store it is mechanical.\n\n\n\nArchictecture of HDD ->",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Q Why system has lot of memory like HDD, RAM \nHDD has mechanical movement inside it, means it has reading writing head, that head actually mechanically moves up, down\nleft,right, forward,backwards, no matter how fast we are doing mechanical movement it will always be slower as compared \nto a electrical movement or movement of electricity. thats why we say our RAM is a primary memory because it is running \non electricity, As soon as power supply is gone the data in RAM is also gone. because it is all current, it is working on\nelectric current. whereas in harddisk whatever we store it is mechanical.\n\n\n\nArchictecture of HDD ->",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
