      "updated": 1771263999278,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "when our read/write head move,based on whihc sector it is, it reads from that sector. and give that data.(16:30)\nNow this is mechanical movement and processor also works electronically at the speed of electricity so it need data very\nfast to process, No matter which processor we are using it take few KB(kilobyte) of data at a time not more than that\n4KB, 8KB, 12KB, .., but the changing speed of the data is very fast, due to this spped if we are going to run with HDD(mechanical)\nmovement there will be a lot of lag. So what we will try to do, we will try to do some storage as form of RAM whihc load the data\nthat can probably be used, or that is being used by the current processes and has a better probabilty of being picked by my\nprocessor",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "when our read/write head move,based on whihc sector it is, it reads from that sector. and give that data.(16:30)\nNow this is mechanical movement and processor also works electronically at the speed of electricity so it need data very\nfast to process, No matter which processor we are using it take few KB(kilobyte) of data at a time not more than that\n4KB, 8KB, 12KB, .., but the changing speed of the data is very fast, due to this spped if we are going to run with HDD(mechanical)\nmovement there will be a lot of lag. So what we will try to do, we will try to do some storage as form of RAM whihc load the data\nthat can probably be used, or that is being used by the current processes and has a better probabilty of being picked by my\nprocessor",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
