      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1771348726988,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "We want our BIOS to boot our OS",
      "fontSize": 28,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "We want our BIOS to boot our OS",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "JKE4fAJF5JZIkGqhCkK2O",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 974.1067351170846,
      "y": 18374.359960827594,
      "width": 1331,
      "height": 150,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bMf",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 505243753,
      "version": 544,
      "versionNonce": 2002248359,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1771350770581,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "as simple as we want our BIOS to boot our OS from HDD\nnot from Optical Disk or anywhere else not from ISO file again and again because ISO file\nis not installed that is just a software because if it goes to ISO file , Optical disk again and again every boot it will\ntry to reinstall, reinstall something that is already there in HDD, So once installed, we are done installing change the\nboot priority and keep HDD on top becuase it is already there, SO it will go to MBR, first sector will redirect to GRUB\nand this will only happen if I am keeping my HDD on top",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "as simple as we want our BIOS to boot our OS from HDD\nnot from Optical Disk or anywhere else not from ISO file again and again because ISO file\nis not installed that is just a software because if it goes to ISO file , Optical disk again and again every boot it will\ntry to reinstall, reinstall something that is already there in HDD, So once installed, we are done installing change the\nboot priority and keep HDD on top becuase it is already there, SO it will go to MBR, first sector will redirect to GRUB\nand this will only happen if I am keeping my HDD on top",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
