    },
    {
      "id": "LxSGDKo8Z4TELdidbOpLR",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1010.1284444831174,
      "y": 27820.35227793765,
      "width": 1210,
      "height": 1300,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bOv",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1703949671,
      "version": 3277,
      "versionNonce": 670504410,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772082066695,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "touch f1 -> it will create empty file f1\nmkdir d1 -> it will create empty directory d1\nls -l -> it will give f1 and d1 with description and somewhere we will see a number that number is\n        in that line the size of that file or directory, To get in a human readable format use \n          ls -lh\nls -lh -> h gives data in human readable format what it will do is? It will convert the size to the\n    maximum possible size like if it can be converted to KBs, it will convert or MB or GB like that\n     it will display maximum possible converstion either be in KB, MB, GB\n     d1 size around 4.0 KB\n\ncd d1 \n\ntouch f{1..5000} -> it will create 5000 empty files inside d1\ncd ..-> go one step back in /root\n\nls -lh -> now the size of d1 is 124 KB\n\ncd d1 -> Go inside d1\nvi dummy -> vi will create and open to edit file if not exist otherwise open it to edit\n            by default this editor is in command mode, So whatever we are writing it would be\n            typed.\n            there are multiple command that we can give to vi\n            i  ->  first we will go to insert mode to do that press i -> they type in one line\n            esc -> again we have to go in command mode to do that press esc, Pointer is on the\n                    same line that we have typed \n            yy   ->  On that same line press y twice, this is basically for coping the line\n                    after pressing yy we would not see any changes but press 2000p, it will \n                    paste same line 20000 times\n            2000p -> it will paste same line 20000 times.\n            p is a shortcut to paste when we will be in command mode these shortcuts will work and 2000\n                for how many times we want to paste\n\n            dd -> is shortcut for deleting a line we will not use right now but should be in command mode\n            now our file has 2000 line now we have big file, we will save and exit to do that :wq\n            \n\n            :wq -> save and exit, w is to save and q is to quit, wq together is for save and exit\n            \n            ls -lh dummy -> it will show the description for dummy size and all its 253 KB\n            \n            cd .. -> /root\n            ls -lh -> now the directory d1 size is 124 KB why?\n\n                when we create a directory in linux, directory is nothing but its a file, but this file\n                stores different kind of data, it just stores pointer and few more details, lets say\n                it will store filename and pointer and whenever we will try to read this file, it has \n                pointer and that pointer is pointing to different file or pointer is pointing to different\n                directory itself and that directory has few more files inside that, it is more like this\n                    why the size of directory increased -> lets say initially it was 4 kb limit for directory\n                     but suddenly we have created 5000 files due to that directory size got increased and \n                    we have creasted one more file that size is 1.5 MB but here it will only store pointer for\n                    that file",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "touch f1 -> it will create empty file f1\nmkdir d1 -> it will create empty directory d1\nls -l -> it will give f1 and d1 with description and somewhere we will see a number that number is\n        in that line the size of that file or directory, To get in a human readable format use \n          ls -lh\nls -lh -> h gives data in human readable format what it will do is? It will convert the size to the\n    maximum possible size like if it can be converted to KBs, it will convert or MB or GB like that\n     it will display maximum possible converstion either be in KB, MB, GB\n     d1 size around 4.0 KB\n\ncd d1 \n\ntouch f{1..5000} -> it will create 5000 empty files inside d1\ncd ..-> go one step back in /root\n\nls -lh -> now the size of d1 is 124 KB\n\ncd d1 -> Go inside d1\nvi dummy -> vi will create and open to edit file if not exist otherwise open it to edit\n            by default this editor is in command mode, So whatever we are writing it would be\n            typed.\n            there are multiple command that we can give to vi\n            i  ->  first we will go to insert mode to do that press i -> they type in one line\n            esc -> again we have to go in command mode to do that press esc, Pointer is on the\n                    same line that we have typed \n            yy   ->  On that same line press y twice, this is basically for coping the line\n                    after pressing yy we would not see any changes but press 2000p, it will \n                    paste same line 20000 times\n            2000p -> it will paste same line 20000 times.\n            p is a shortcut to paste when we will be in command mode these shortcuts will work and 2000\n                for how many times we want to paste\n\n            dd -> is shortcut for deleting a line we will not use right now but should be in command mode\n            now our file has 2000 line now we have big file, we will save and exit to do that :wq\n            \n\n            :wq -> save and exit, w is to save and q is to quit, wq together is for save and exit\n            \n            ls -lh dummy -> it will show the description for dummy size and all its 253 KB\n            \n            cd .. -> /root\n            ls -lh -> now the directory d1 size is 124 KB why?\n\n                when we create a directory in linux, directory is nothing but its a file, but this file\n                stores different kind of data, it just stores pointer and few more details, lets say\n                it will store filename and pointer and whenever we will try to read this file, it has \n                pointer and that pointer is pointing to different file or pointer is pointing to different\n                directory itself and that directory has few more files inside that, it is more like this\n                    why the size of directory increased -> lets say initially it was 4 kb limit for directory\n                     but suddenly we have created 5000 files due to that directory size got increased and \n                    we have creasted one more file that size is 1.5 MB but here it will only store pointer for\n                    that file",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "fGhcqWkThbTbLzrRQUCBA",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1007.4888700939443,
