      "updated": 1772083824652,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Why do we use CLI(Command Line Interface) why not GUI(Graphical User interface)?",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Why do we use CLI(Command Line Interface) why not GUI(Graphical User interface)?",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "0NZnvz--_zbEmqN5IIWh8",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1034.9964834854989,
      "y": 30931.196171940366,
      "width": 1166,
      "height": 725,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#b2f2bb",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bOy",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1084775241,
      "version": 3596,
      "versionNonce": 2079928538,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772083820985,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "CLI is fast but that is not a main reason.\nFirst of all GUI is not that powerful. We might notice at one part  or our screen there is time\nvisible, But now we know behind that time there is date command running continuously and updating\nthe time Which means behind every GUI that we see, there is some CLI that is running, But CLI has\nso many commands, If we will make GUI for all command then our entire system will be filled by \nGUI only, we won't be able to do anything else and all the GUI of the world is not needed also because\neveryone is going to use it, Those are going to use it at that deeper level or at that deeper\nunderstanding whinc means they are already developers they are already engineers they can figure out\na way to do it with commands also so that is why GUI is one thing which is not that powerful. which\nis not that big enough. CLI gives us optimization at a way deeper level.\n\nLets say in Windows it we see task manager, task manager is a way to manage our processor, RAM and \neverything But can it give us a control of restricting the number of thread on each and every process\n-> No but CLI can, CLI is that level powerful. And obviously those who understand threads and restricting\nthreads and everything they dont even need GUI for it, They can work with CLI, CLI is way more\npowerful than GUI, it gives us more options or way more deeper things to do but that is still not the\nmain reason, the problem is lets say we are working with GUI, with CLI the thing is we are writing \ncommands like command c1, c2, c3 and whatever we want that is done, right now we are doing via \ncommmands. Later on we will write all these commands in a file and we will call this is a script. And \nwe will run this script manually that is called as scripting Now after that next stage is rather than\nrunning all these command written in a file as a script manually, we will run on the basis of certain\ntrigger, Trigger as in lets say someone log into our system we have to run this file or every night \n12 O clock, we have to run this file that is called as Automation. So with CLI we can automate things.\nThe thing is with GUI also we can automate but GUI automation has a limitation. Why it has a limitation ?\nbecause lets say our screen is that big lets say at a time it can display one process or two process or \nfour process so more than 4 process we can't automate at the very same time. Whatever other processess are\nthere , they are not visible on our GUI, But with CLI we can just write all these commands in a script\nand they can keep on running in backgroud, In foreground we are doing whatever we are doing or we are just\ndoing nothing that is also fine. So CLI gives us the power of scripting and automation.(1:3: 30)",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "CLI is fast but that is not a main reason.\nFirst of all GUI is not that powerful. We might notice at one part  or our screen there is time\nvisible, But now we know behind that time there is date command running continuously and updating\nthe time Which means behind every GUI that we see, there is some CLI that is running, But CLI has\nso many commands, If we will make GUI for all command then our entire system will be filled by \nGUI only, we won't be able to do anything else and all the GUI of the world is not needed also because\neveryone is going to use it, Those are going to use it at that deeper level or at that deeper\nunderstanding whinc means they are already developers they are already engineers they can figure out\na way to do it with commands also so that is why GUI is one thing which is not that powerful. which\nis not that big enough. CLI gives us optimization at a way deeper level.\n\nLets say in Windows it we see task manager, task manager is a way to manage our processor, RAM and \neverything But can it give us a control of restricting the number of thread on each and every process\n-> No but CLI can, CLI is that level powerful. And obviously those who understand threads and restricting\nthreads and everything they dont even need GUI for it, They can work with CLI, CLI is way more\npowerful than GUI, it gives us more options or way more deeper things to do but that is still not the\nmain reason, the problem is lets say we are working with GUI, with CLI the thing is we are writing \ncommands like command c1, c2, c3 and whatever we want that is done, right now we are doing via \ncommmands. Later on we will write all these commands in a file and we will call this is a script. And \nwe will run this script manually that is called as scripting Now after that next stage is rather than\nrunning all these command written in a file as a script manually, we will run on the basis of certain\ntrigger, Trigger as in lets say someone log into our system we have to run this file or every night \n12 O clock, we have to run this file that is called as Automation. So with CLI we can automate things.\nThe thing is with GUI also we can automate but GUI automation has a limitation. Why it has a limitation ?\nbecause lets say our screen is that big lets say at a time it can display one process or two process or \nfour process so more than 4 process we can't automate at the very same time. Whatever other processess are\nthere , they are not visible on our GUI, But with CLI we can just write all these commands in a script\nand they can keep on running in backgroud, In foreground we are doing whatever we are doing or we are just\ndoing nothing that is also fine. So CLI gives us the power of scripting and automation.(1:3: 30)",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
